Janne Viljami "Warman" Wirman (born 26 April 1979) is a Finnish musician; he is the former keyboardist for the Finnish metal band Children of Bodom from 1997 to 2019 and currently collaborating with Warmen.
For most of his early life, he focused his style on jazz, switching his main interest to heavy metal music once he joined the metal band Children of Bodom in 1997.
In the year of 2000, Wirman assembled progressive metal band Warmen as his main side-project.

Thus, in early 2002, Wirman took part in the recording of Masterplan's self-titled debut album.
To record with Warmen, Wirman built the Warmen Productions Studio (now named Beyond Abilities).
